Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 28
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 28

Reconsideration — Clear Error, New Evidence, Change in Law

⚖️ Core Message

Use reconsideration sparingly and with precision.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Grounds: (1) clear error; (2) new evidence; (3) intervening law.
2. Identify the specific page/line of the order and the controlling citation.
3. Attach the new evidence; explain why it wasn’t available earlier.
4. Ask for limited relief or clarification to enable review.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 1‑page Motion for Reconsideration citing exact lines, a controlling case, and a narrowly tailored fix.
✅ Model Response

MOTION FOR RECONSIDERATION (excerpt)

1. The Order at p.3 n.2 applies an incorrect standard (cite).

2. New evidence attached as Ex. A could not be obtained earlier.

3. Relief: clarify that the Court did not reach Winter factor (b).

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Surgical, not sprawling.
🎨 Visual Concept

A scalpel over a tiny highlighted line of an order.
